                    </div>
                    <span>In my opinion, it's one of the best books on the subject, and it is for a reason that this textbook is used in Berkeley's undergraduate EE/CS database CS186 course. I read reviews below from some of the straight 'A' students that the book is too complex and confusing. Others complain it doesn't cover common DBMS vendor implementations (Oracle, SQL). Again, this is a well-written book that thoroughly covers the theory behind every vendor's database design, and it's difficult to see why one would expect it to be an easy reading. If you like serious, unwatered-down textbook style reading that requires some thought on your part then this book is right for you.</span>
                  
